Dillen Bloomgren was pronounced dead at St. Joseph's Hospital in Dickinson, of a gunshot wound to the head, authorities said. Dunn County Deputy Glen Gietzen said the boys were hunting with their two other brothers and their father during the state's youth pheasant season when the shooting happened Sunday afternoon, north of Gladstone.
